# Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only for the edrilla admin panel (Vite SPA).
#
# WHY A HEADER, NOT A <meta> TAG:
#   Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only is only valid as an HTTP response header;
#   browsers ignore it in <meta http-equiv>. Serve it from nginx (or whatever
#   static host fronts the built SPA).
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   Copy the `add_header` line below into the nginx `server { }` block that
#   serves this app's `dist/` output (the same block that has the SPA
#   `try_files ... /index.html` fallback), then `nginx -t && nginx -s reload`.
#   Report-only means NOTHING is blocked - violations are only reported
#   (browser console, and to `report-uri` if you enable one).
#
# ORIGIN INVENTORY (why each source is listed):
#   script-src:
#     https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com   Quill 1.3.7 loaded at runtime
#                                    (src/pages/courses/components/EditTextLesson.tsx).
#     https://connect.facebook.net   Facebook embed SDK (src/components/FacebookEmbed.js).
#     NOTE: no 'unsafe-inline' - the built admin app ships NO inline scripts
#     (index.html is clean). The dev server header in vite.config.ts adds it
#     only because @vitejs/plugin-react injects an inline refresh preamble.
#   style-src:
#     https://fonts.googleapis.com   Outfit font @import (src/index.css line 1).
#     https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com   quill.snow.min.css (EditTextLesson.tsx).
#     'unsafe-inline'                Tailwind/React inline styles. Acceptable
#                                    initially; tighten later (step 3).
#   font-src:    https://fonts.gstatic.com (Google Fonts files).
#   img-src:     https://api.edrilla.com (VITE_IMAGE_URL uploads), placehold.co +
#                https://*.mm.bing.net + static.vecteezy.com (hardcoded fallback
#                thumbnails/avatars in CourseList/StudenList/Banner/etc.),
#                https://www.facebook.com (FB embed tracking pixel), data:/blob:.
#   media-src:   https://api.edrilla.com + blob:/data: (uploaded media previews).
#   connect-src: https://api.edrilla.com + wss://api.edrilla.com (REST via
#                VITE_BASE_URL + socket.io chat in src/services/chatService.ts).
#   frame-src:   https://www.youtube.com (YoutubeEmbed.js + video components),
#                https://platform.twitter.com (TwitterEmbed.js Tweet.html iframe),
#                https://www.facebook.com (FB SDK xfbml post iframes).
#   worker-src:  blob: ('self' kept for safety with bundled workers).
#
# TIGHTENING STEPS (in order, after a clean reporting period):
#   1. Enable report collection: append `report-uri https://api.edrilla.com/csp-report;`
#      (endpoint must accept POST application/csp-report) so you see violations
#      from real users, not just your own console.
#   2. Once reports are quiet for ~2 weeks, rename the header to
#      Content-Security-Policy (enforcing). Keep the report-uri.
#   3. Longer term: drop 'unsafe-inline' from style-src, replace the hardcoded
#      bing/vecteezy/placehold fallback images with bundled assets so img-src
#      can shrink to 'self' + api.edrilla.com, and self-host Quill instead of
#      loading it from cdnjs at runtime.
#
# Dev parity: vite.config.ts sends the same header (plus localhost/HMR and
# 'unsafe-inline' script allowances for the React refresh preamble) from the
# dev server so violations surface in the console now.

add_header Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only "default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'self'; form-action 'self'; script-src 'self' https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com https://connect.facebook.net; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com data:; img-src 'self' data: blob: https://api.edrilla.com https://placehold.co https://*.mm.bing.net https://static.vecteezy.com https://www.facebook.com; media-src 'self' blob: data: https://api.edrilla.com; connect-src 'self' https://api.edrilla.com wss://api.edrilla.com; frame-src 'self' https://www.youtube.com https://platform.twitter.com https://www.facebook.com; worker-src 'self' blob:" always;
